# Snakemake CLI

On this machine, `snakemake` is not guaranteed to be on the default shell `PATH`. It is available in a **conda environment named `snakemake`** (e.g. `conda activate snakemake` before running `snakemake -n`, lint, or DAG checks). Workflow rule execution still uses per-rule conda envs via `--use-conda`.
